Chilean Stocks: BCI, Cap, Empresas La Polar, Lan Airlines

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-18T21:15:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/chilean-stocks-bci-cap-empresas-la-polar-lan-airlines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.4 percent to 4,313.64.    Banco de Credito e Inversiones (BCI)   rose 1 percent to
29,780 pesos. Chile’s fourth-largest lender had its rating
increased to “buy” from “hold” at Banchile-Citi, the joint
research department of Chilean lender Banco de Chile and
Citigroup Inc.    Cap SA (CAP)   increased 2.7 percent to 22,337 pesos, its
second day of gains. Chile’s largest steel producer and iron
miner rose on speculation that  Japan  will have to import more
steel for reconstruction efforts after last week’s earthquake
and tsunami.    Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 5.1 percent to
2,378.7 pesos. The department store operator has lost 13 percent
in the past two days, the steepest two-day decline since October
2008, after reporting lower-than-forecast profits for 2010.    Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   lost 1.7 percent to 11,890 pesos,
its lowest price since July 2010. Latin America’s largest
airline by market value fell after a Chilean tribunal decided to
proceed with a review of its planned takeover of  Brazil ’s Tam
SA, rejecting an appeal that would have sped-up the process.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
